title: Rage Against the Chainring
description: Each event will consist of a 50 mile and 25 mile course. While challenging they are designed to accommodate riders of all skill.
course: Courses will be open course and the event is self supported. We will release a gps file of the course and have maps and cue sheets available at the event. All turns will be marked.
registration: There is day of registration for each of the events. This starts at 7 am and ends approximately 15 minutes before the start of the event.

title: Tour de Trees
description: The 4th Annual Tour de Trees and EcoFest at the Arb takes place Sunday.  The bike ride starts at 10:00 and EcoFest is  from 1:00-6:00 pm at beautiful Bartlett Arboretum in Belle Plaine, KS,Sunday October 29th. This event is an afternoon of immersion in care-taking of the earth, the body, and the soul. Enjoy live music powered by bicycle generators, yoga, environmental speakers, fresh local food, swing-powered art, and eco-centric kids' activities set against a backdrop of autumn splendor. Attendees who arrive by bicycle receive free admission.  Enjoy a cold beer from Walnut River Brewing, our 2017 Beer sponser.  Also, enjoy some Hatch Pork Green Chile Verde, plus we will have a vegetarian Green Chile option as well made by local foodie Joe Stumpe.
course: The Course will start at the Bartlett Arboretum and will be either a 60 or 25 mile gravel road course
directions: Exit I35 at the Mulvane exit, continue east to Hillside ave and go south 3 miles to Belle Plaine Kansas
